      Iterable<? extends Command> getDstWhCommands()
      Returns a Iterable to send to a hive driver on the source warehouse If you *need* a List instead, you can use guava's ImmutableList.copyOf(iterable) or Lists.newArrayList(iterable) to get the underlying list, but this defeats the purpose of making this interface an Iterable rather than a List, since it is very likely that the number of Commands returned here will cause your process to run OOM.

      • needsStagingDirs

        public boolean needsStagingDirs()
        Description copied from class: ReplicationTask
        Returns true if the replication task in question needs to create staging directories to complete its operation. This will mean that you will need to copy these directories over to the destination warehouse for each source-destination warehouse pair. If this is true, you will need to call .withSrcStagingDirProvider(...) and .withDstStagingDirProvider(...) before this ReplicationTask is usable
